{"title": "Elon Musk's BiPAP Machines May Be Better Than Nothing, at Least", "link": "https://gizmodo.com/elon-musks-bipap-machines-may-be-better-than-nothing-a-1842653470", "description": "<img src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/s--2_DASsBj--/c_fit,fl_progressive,q_80,w_636/jekfevtvt8hrwsmtdwbh.jpg\" /><p>Tesla and SpaceX CEO Elon Musk said he’d be sending desperately needed “FDA-approved ventilators” to hard-hit hospitals across the nation dealing with the coronavirus crisis—but they haven’t been the high-grade kind needed to keep intensive care patients alive. Instead, those sent off so far appear to be Bilevel…</p><p><a href=\"https://gizmodo.com/elon-musks-bipap-machines-may-be-better-than-nothing-a-1842653470\">Read more...</a></p>", "date": "Fri, 03 Apr 2020 02:15:00 GMT", "categories": ["elon musk", "ventilators", "cpap", "bipap", "coronavirus", "health", "covid 19", "sars cov 2", "technology"], "source": "Gizmodo", "sentiment": "positive"}
