{"title": "CDC is expected to tell Americans to wear cloth masks, save medical masks for health workers", "link": "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Techcrunch/~3/iC3hsbZkgAo/", "description": "On Thursday, the White House said that it will likely soon adjust previous guidelines that discouraged non-health workers from wearing face masks. The change would be issued as &#8220;guidance&#8221; from the CDC, but according to the president—who continues to hesitate at exerting federal power during the COVID-19 crisis—it will not be made mandatory. Supplies of [&#8230;]", "date": "Fri, 03 Apr 2020 01:04:52 +0000", "categories": ["Health", "TC", "coronavirus", "COVID-19"], "source": "TechCrunch", "sentiment": "positive"}
{"title": "Instacart will provide shoppers with free masks and hand sanitizers", "link": "https://www.engadget.com/2020-04-03-instacart-health-safety-kits.html", "description": "\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=\"https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/LcT9J67TBDoiQ6lKTNkDJA--~B/dz0xNjAwO2g9OTk5O2FwcGlkPXl0YWNoeW9u/https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?crop=1400%2C874%2C0%2C41&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;resize=1600%2C999&amp;image_uri=https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-04/c1b314a0-756f-11ea-9b04-04fe825df6fa&amp;client=a1acac3e1b3290917d92&amp;signature=aff0b69e65216b1606416a71fb322fc0711beae3\" /><p>Instacart will <a href=\"https://medium.com/shopper-news/distributing-health-safety-kits-for-shoppers-a4d023932647\">start distributing</a> free health and safety kit to its full-service shoppers next week. The move likely comes as a response to the <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/2020-03-30-instacart-workers-go-on-strike-despite-concessions.html\">walkout</a> workers <a href=\"https://medium.com/@GigWorkersCollective/instacart-emergency-walk-off-ebdf11b6995a\">staged</a> a few days ago to protest the company&#39;s inadequate safety measures against the coronavirus pandemic. One of their demands was the distribution of items like hand sanitizers.</p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The grocery delivery service&#39;s kits will contain washable and reusable cloth face masks, which will not have an impact on supplies for the healthcare and medical community. They will also contain ethyl alcohol-based hand sanitizers and forehead thermometers that can check temperatures in 15 seconds.</p>\n\n<p>Instacart explained that up until now, the CDC has only recommended social distancing and frequent hand washing to prevent the spread of COVID-19. However, it understands &quot;that the situation continues to evolve quickly,&quot; so it took &quot;proactive steps to secure face masks and thermometers&quot; and manufactured hand sanitizers for shoppers. It&#39;s worth noting that the White House is soon <a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2020/04/02/coronavirus-facemasks-policyreversal/\">expected</a> to urge Americans to wear cloth masks or any material they can use to cover their face.</p>\n\n<p>It&#39;s unclear if the company is meeting all the demands made by the workers who walked out. But shortly after the strike was announced, it <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/27/instacart-updates-pay-safety-guidelines-as-workers-plan-monday-strike.html\">updated</a> its policy to provide up to 14 days of paid sick leave to workers diagnosed with or are quarantined due to COVID-19. It also promised bonus pay for in-store shoppers based on the number of hours worked.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t", "date": "Fri, 03 Apr 2020 03:08:00 -0400", "categories": ["business", "instacart"], "source": "Engadget RSS Feed", "sentiment": "positive"}
